The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Monday, February 23, 2004 				 DMK wants shine off BJP
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 																								Virdhunagar (Tamil Nadu), Feb. 22: The DMK today fired the first salvo at erstwhile ally BJP in the run-up to the Lok Sabha elections, calling upon the Election Commission to immediately stop the caretaker NDA governments India Shining campaign. 																								The party, which has stitched an alliance against the NDA in the state, adopted a resolution at its conference here condemning the BJP-led NDA for spending crores and crores of rupees from the public exchequer. 																								Stating that the governments move violated the spirit of the model code of conduct for political parties, the DMK accused the Vajpayee regime of trying to take advantage over others through the publicity blitz in newspapers and the electronic media, ignoring the Nirvachan Sadan directives. Fight vs Jaya, not Atal																								The DMK-led front launched its Lok Sabha campaign at a rally attended by several lakh people near this town this evening. At the show of strength at Kamarajs birthplace, DMK chief M. Karunanidhi termed the battle as being against the Advani-Jayalalithaa alliance. This is not a fight against the Vajpayee-led alliance for it was Advani who firmed up the alliance with the ADMK leader in the state.																								Reducing the Lok Sabha battle into a fight between the DMK and the ADMK, the Opposition  the CPI, CPM, MDMK and PMK focused the attack on Jayalalithaa. Only state Congress chief G.K. Vasan made a forceful plea for making Sonia Gandhi the next Prime Minister.
